The Great Wall of China is one of the most iconic and recognizable landmarks in the world, and its significance in history is immense. Built over a period of more than 2,000 years, the wall was constructed to protect China from invading armies and to control trade and immigration. It was a massive undertaking that required the labor of millions of people and the use of advanced engineering techniques.

1. Bias and discrimination: AI systems can perpetuate and even exacerbate existing biases and discrimination in healthcare.
